BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Jazz Talks with Trey Wright
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260813T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260813T203000
DTSTAMP:20260711T043903Z
UID:occ-1235@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Lecture
DESCRIPTION:Coltrane's A Love Supreme\, unpacked by jazz guitarist and KSU
  professor Trey Wright\; 30 seats\, 21+\, drink included.\n\nAn interactiv
 e talk on John Coltrane and A Love Supreme\, his 1965 landmark\, led by Tr
 ey Wright\, who teaches jazz guitar and jazz history at Kennesaw State. Wr
 ight is a working guitarist himself: he has played the Montreux Jazz Festi
 val\, and his trio's album Thinking Out Loud reached the first round of Gr
 ammy consideration in the jazz instrumental category. Part of the Jazz At 
 The Strand series. Admission includes one drink ticket\; seating is capped
  at 30\, and guests must be 21 or older.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260711T043436Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 06zRHZMA2
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Silent Film at The Strand: Sunrise (1927)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260816T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260816T170000
DTSTAMP:20260711T043903Z
UID:occ-1240@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Film Screening
DESCRIPTION:F.W. Murnau's 1927 silent masterpiece\, scored live on the Mig
 hty Allen Theatre Organ by house organist Ron Carter.\n\nF.W. Murnau's sil
 ent classic follows a farmer torn between a seductive woman from the city 
 and the wife he has left waiting at home. It won at the very first Academy
  Awards and is still counted among the most visually inventive films ever 
 made. House organist Ron Carter accompanies live on the Strand Theatre's M
 ighty Allen\, a four-manual digital replica of a 1920s Wurlitzer complete 
 with a toy counter of train whistles\, car horns\, and gunshots. An organ 
 pops concert begins thirty minutes before showtime\; the film runs 97 minu
 tes.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260711T043436Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 074Co9MAE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Ferris Bueller's Day Off (1986)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260820T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260820T210000
DTSTAMP:20260711T043903Z
UID:occ-1239@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Film Screening
DESCRIPTION:John Hughes's 1986 comedy of epic truancy\, with a Mighty Alle
 n Theatre Organ concert beforehand.\n\nJohn Hughes's 1986 comedy about Fer
 ris Bueller (Matthew Broderick)\, a high school senior who fakes sick and 
 spends one glorious day loose in Chicago with his girlfriend\, his anxious
  best friend\, and a borrowed 1961 Ferrari\, while his dean hunts him down
 . Ferris narrates straight to the camera the whole way. The house Mighty A
 llen Theatre Organ plays a half-hour concert before the film starts. 1 hou
 r 43 minutes\, rated PG-13.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260711T043436Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 074DYvMAM
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mamma Mia! and Margaritas!
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260822T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260822T170000
DTSTAMP:20260711T043903Z
UID:occ-1657@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Film Screening
DESCRIPTION:The 2008 ABBA movie musical on the big screen\, with a margari
 ta bar and a pre-show organ concert.\n\nThe 2008 film of the ABBA jukebox 
 musical: on a Greek island\, a bride-to-be finds three men in her mother's
  old diary who might be her father\, and quietly adds all of them to the g
 uest list — mom Donna (Meryl Streep) none the wiser. Pierce Brosnan\, Co
 lin Firth\, and Stellan Skarsgård are the candidates. The Strand Theatre 
 sells margaritas\, frozen or on the rocks\, and boas are encouraged. A liv
 e concert on the house's Mighty Allen Theatre Organ starts thirty minutes 
 before the film. 1 hour 48 minutes\, rated PG-13.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260711T043436Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 075UavMAE
END:VEVENT
