BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Shrek (2001)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260923T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260923T170000
DTSTAMP:20260711T043903Z
UID:occ-1661@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Film Screening
DESCRIPTION:DreamWorks' 2001 fairy-tale spoof on the big screen — Mike M
 yers' ogre\, Eddie Murphy's Donkey\, 89 minutes\, PG.\n\nThe 2001 DreamWor
 ks comedy that won the first-ever Oscar for Best Animated Feature\, back o
 n a big screen. An ogre who just wants his swamp to himself strikes a deal
  with the fussy Lord Farquaad: rescue Princess Fiona\, get the fairy-tale 
 squatters off his land. Mike Myers voices Shrek in the Scottish accent he 
 insisted on re-recording every line to get\, with Eddie Murphy\, Cameron D
 iaz\, and John Lithgow rounding out the cast\, plus a Smash Mouth-heavy so
 undtrack that dates it precisely and fondly. Loosely based on William Stei
 g's picture book. 89 minutes\, rated PG.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260711T043436Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 075VwnMAE
END:VEVENT
