BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sparrows (1926)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260927T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260927T170000
DTSTAMP:20260711T043903Z
UID:occ-942@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Film Screening
DESCRIPTION:Mary Pickford's 1926 silent melodrama\, screened with live acc
 ompaniment on the Mighty Allen Theatre Organ.\n\nMary Pickford plays Molly
 \, the oldest of a band of orphans held captive on a baby farm deep in an 
 alligator-infested swamp\, who plots their escape when the children's crue
 l keeper decides to be rid of one of them. Part of the Strand Theatre's Si
 lent Film Series\, with house organist Ron Carter providing a live score o
 n the Mighty Allen Theatre Organ\, whose digital toy counter supplies whis
 tles\, thunder\, and gunshots on cue. An organ pops concert begins thirty 
 minutes before the film. Runs 1 hour 49 minutes\; not rated.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260711T043436Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 06X9ttMAC
END:VEVENT
